===Etymology===
[[w:Hiram Codd|Hiram Codd]], a British manufacturer of [[soft drink]]s, [[patent]]ed several designs for mineral water bottles in the 1870s + [[wallop|WALLOP]], a [[beer]] drinker’s [[pejorative]] reference to soft drink.
There is an absence of [[evidence]] supporting this. The suggestion is further discredited by early spellings of the term. [http://oed.com/bbcwords/codswallop-new.html OED Online-BBC Balderdash and Piffle]

